1
00:00:46,592 --> 00:00:47,889
Stay down.

2
00:01:00,505 --> 00:01:02,598
Freeze! Just freeze.

3
00:01:43,949 --> 00:01:46,144
Your hands ever shake, Frank?

4
00:01:46,551 --> 00:01:47,882
Sometimes.

5
00:01:49,054 --> 00:01:50,544
lt's just adrenaline.

6
00:01:56,795 --> 00:01:57,887
Of course.

7
00:01:58,063 --> 00:01:59,792
How did you know?

8
00:02:00,298 --> 00:02:02,562
-l saw him washing the car.
-So did l.

9
00:02:03,301 --> 00:02:06,065
They don't wash cars
on the parking levels.

10
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:15,741
Frank...

11
00:02:15,981 --> 00:02:17,812
...l'd like you to stay on.

12
00:02:19,084 --> 00:02:21,678
l'm no good in a permanent position.

13
00:02:22,254 --> 00:02:23,983
My feet go to sleep.

14
00:03:48,507 --> 00:03:51,271
You're turning down $2,000 a week?

15
00:03:53,845 --> 00:03:57,838
So you won't protect Rachel Marron
because she's in show business?

16
00:03:58,016 --> 00:03:59,574
l don't do celebrities.

17
00:04:00,185 --> 00:04:01,174
2500.

18
00:04:01,353 --> 00:04:03,583
There's many good men for that much.

19
00:04:03,789 --> 00:04:05,086
Have you talked to...

20
00:04:05,357 --> 00:04:07,348
...Racine, Fitzgerald...

21
00:04:07,926 --> 00:04:09,086
...Portman?

22
00:04:09,294 --> 00:04:10,852
Portman's interested.

23
00:04:11,296 --> 00:04:13,787
But we heard you were the best.

24
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:16,362
There's no such thing.

25
00:04:16,868 --> 00:04:21,362
We're talking about a very frightened
lady with an 8-year-old son.

26
00:04:21,606 --> 00:04:24,439
l wouldn't be here if l
didn't think this was real.

27
00:04:26,711 --> 00:04:29,202
Farmer, she begged me to get you.

28
00:04:30,115 --> 00:04:31,548
Please.

29
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:33,941
Okay, l'll come.

30
00:04:34,886 --> 00:04:37,047
l'll look the situation over.

31
00:04:38,957 --> 00:04:40,219
lf l take it...

32
00:04:40,826 --> 00:04:42,453
...it's 3000 a week.

33
00:04:43,461 --> 00:04:46,328
You must be very deadly
for 3 grand a week.

34
00:04:47,132 --> 00:04:48,622
Watch and see.

35
00:04:53,471 --> 00:04:54,460
Shit.

36
00:04:54,639 --> 00:04:56,072
lt's something.

37
00:05:00,879 --> 00:05:01,607
Sorry.

38
00:05:05,917 --> 00:05:07,646
Don't stand there, either.

39
00:05:59,905 --> 00:06:02,203
Frank Farmer to see Miss Marron.

40
00:06:02,908 --> 00:06:04,136
What?

41
00:06:05,977 --> 00:06:08,639
Alexander Graham Bell
to see Miss Marron.

42
00:06:09,481 --> 00:06:11,210
Got an appointment?

43
00:06:17,155 --> 00:06:19,988
The atomic number of zinc is thirty.

44
00:06:20,725 --> 00:06:21,817
All right.

45
00:07:28,793 --> 00:07:30,385
Can l help you?

46
00:07:32,998 --> 00:07:34,625
You the man on the intercom?

47
00:07:37,235 --> 00:07:38,634
Can l help you?

48
00:07:38,903 --> 00:07:41,133
My name's Edison.
l have an appointment.

49
00:07:43,241 --> 00:07:44,503
Arranged by...?

50
00:07:45,076 --> 00:07:46,475
Mr. Devaney.

51
00:07:50,081 --> 00:07:51,639
Go right ahead, Mr. Edison.

52
00:07:52,150 --> 00:07:53,310
What happened?

53
00:07:55,253 --> 00:07:56,515
A doll.

54
00:08:12,904 --> 00:08:14,633
Henry Ford to see Mr. Devaney.

55
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,070
Who?

56
00:08:16,307 --> 00:08:17,467
Henry Ford.

57
00:08:18,410 --> 00:08:19,399
Come in.

58
00:09:33,718 --> 00:09:35,208
Playback, everybody.

59
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:41,483
That's what l want.

60
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:45,723
Glad you came. Come on.
l'll introduce you to Rachel.

61
00:09:46,998 --> 00:09:48,989
l bet you loved it.

62
00:09:49,334 --> 00:09:52,497
-He doesn't know great art.
-Frank Farmer's here.

63
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:55,400
-Do you think this is me?
-lt's terrific.

64
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,171
-Frank Farmer's here.
-Who?

65
00:09:57,342 --> 00:09:59,071
Frank Farmer. The bodyguard.

66
00:09:59,244 --> 00:10:01,576
l think Rory should be my bodyguard.

67
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:05,240
Raise your butt and come meet him.

68
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:09,352
All right. l'm up.

69
00:10:13,191 --> 00:10:14,590
Frank Farmer...

70
00:10:15,026 --> 00:10:16,084
...Rachel Marron.

71
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,928
You don't look like a bodyguard.

72
00:10:25,537 --> 00:10:27,198
What'd you expect?

73
00:10:27,772 --> 00:10:29,603
Maybe a tough guy.

74
00:10:31,109 --> 00:10:32,599
This is my disguise.

75
00:10:35,046 --> 00:10:36,377
His timing's good.

76
00:10:36,948 --> 00:10:40,611
This is Nicki, Rachel's sister
and personal secretary.

77
00:10:40,785 --> 00:10:42,218
Nice to meet you.

78
00:10:42,387 --> 00:10:43,285
Tony Scibelli.

79
00:10:45,056 --> 00:10:46,455
Sy Spector, publicist.

80
00:10:48,726 --> 00:10:50,125
Can we get you a drink?

81
00:10:50,795 --> 00:10:52,126
An orange juice.

82
00:10:52,797 --> 00:10:53,786
Straight?

83
00:11:02,140 --> 00:11:03,732
This is Bill's idea.

84
00:11:04,242 --> 00:11:06,403
A sudden obsession with protecting me.

85
00:11:07,078 --> 00:11:09,911
Tony's always done my security
and we've done just fine.

86
00:11:10,081 --> 00:11:11,571
ls this what we talked about?

87
00:11:11,749 --> 00:11:14,650
Bill's right. lt's time
you took more precautions.

88
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:18,981
l'm sure they'll say the number of
nuts writing fan letters jumps...

89
00:11:19,157 --> 00:11:21,148
...whenever Rachel's on a magazine.

90
00:11:21,326 --> 00:11:22,657
Not like this.

91
00:11:22,827 --> 00:11:24,419
Relax, guys.

92
00:11:24,596 --> 00:11:28,157
l said l'll do it, so l will.
See what l'm dealing with?

93
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,764
l'll do this as long as
we understand each other.

94
00:11:32,103 --> 00:11:34,663
l won't let this thing alter my life.

95
00:11:34,839 --> 00:11:37,000
Honey, that won't be a problem.

96
00:11:37,175 --> 00:11:41,009
Rachel's household is informal.
We're all on a first-name basis.

97
00:11:41,179 --> 00:11:42,771
You'll fit in fine.

98
00:11:42,947 --> 00:11:45,939
Choose whatever alarm system
you want for the house.

99
00:11:46,117 --> 00:11:48,847
lmproved security for the gate.
What else?

100
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,851
What else?

101
00:11:51,456 --> 00:11:54,118
l think l'm safe when l'm at the house.

102
00:11:54,292 --> 00:11:56,852
-So the main thing is when l go out.
-Exactly.

103
00:11:57,028 --> 00:12:01,124
Tony will fill you in. l don't want you
falling all over me everywhere l go.

104
00:12:01,532 --> 00:12:05,525
Fletcher cannot be affected.

105
00:12:05,703 --> 00:12:09,139
l'll cover that. We'll tell him
you've got some other function.

106
00:12:09,307 --> 00:12:13,300
l don't want him to think he's in prison.
So the estate must not be altered.

107
00:12:13,478 --> 00:12:16,038
He shouldn't even know you're here.

108
00:12:17,649 --> 00:12:20,049
There's been a misunderstanding.

109
00:12:20,218 --> 00:12:23,051
So if you'll show me the way out,
l'll save us both trouble.

110
00:12:23,221 --> 00:12:24,188
By the pool.

111
00:12:27,558 --> 00:12:29,150
lt was nice meeting you.

112
00:12:29,494 --> 00:12:30,552
Or the entry door.

113
00:12:30,895 --> 00:12:33,159
Shut up. Wait a minute!

114
00:12:33,331 --> 00:12:35,231
We shouldn't beg this guy.

115
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:39,166
l'm handling this. Farmer,
would you wait a minute?

116
00:12:41,839 --> 00:12:45,673
l should have told you more.
l was afraid she wouldn't do it.

117
00:12:45,843 --> 00:12:48,334
l thought l'd let you two work it out.

118
00:12:48,513 --> 00:12:49,571
We did.

119
00:12:49,747 --> 00:12:53,740
She's not a bad person and whether
she knows it or not, she needs you.

120
00:12:54,585 --> 00:12:58,919
You've come this far, wait a moment.
l must show you something.

121
00:13:00,591 --> 00:13:02,024
Please, Farmer.

122
00:13:27,452 --> 00:13:28,942
How are you today?

123
00:13:30,388 --> 00:13:32,049
Fine. And you?

124
00:13:32,557 --> 00:13:35,117
Oh, l'm fine. Do you like boats?

125
00:13:37,795 --> 00:13:39,786
No, l don't like boats.

126
00:13:40,665 --> 00:13:41,654
Why not?

127
00:13:41,899 --> 00:13:42,957
l don't know.

128
00:13:43,468 --> 00:13:46,733
Sure you do. But you
don't want to tell me.

129
00:13:47,638 --> 00:13:49,230
You're a smart kid.

130
00:13:51,409 --> 00:13:53,468
One time l was...

131
00:13:54,078 --> 00:13:56,808
...stuck on a boat with
some people for 4 months.

132
00:13:57,081 --> 00:13:58,139
A lifeboat?

133
00:13:58,483 --> 00:13:59,973
No, it was a...

134
00:14:00,251 --> 00:14:02,082
...big, white yacht.

135
00:14:03,254 --> 00:14:05,313
You're the bodyguard, aren't you?

136
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:06,980
What do you know about it?

137
00:14:07,425 --> 00:14:08,915
l've got ears.

138
00:14:10,495 --> 00:14:12,087
l'll remember that.

139
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:18,493
This is just in the last 6 months.

140
00:14:19,270 --> 00:14:22,171
Have you ever had these
professionally assessed?

141
00:14:23,107 --> 00:14:26,440
-l heard you were in the Secret Service.
-That's right.

142
00:14:27,678 --> 00:14:29,009
You guard the main man?

143
00:14:30,114 --> 00:14:32,776
l was 2 years with
Carter, 4 with Reagan.

144
00:14:33,117 --> 00:14:34,448
Reagan got shot.

145
00:14:36,788 --> 00:14:38,278
Not on my shift.

146
00:14:40,057 --> 00:14:41,046
Good.

147
00:14:41,292 --> 00:14:42,953
This could be something.

148
00:14:45,196 --> 00:14:48,791
Do you think it could be the
same guy who rigged the doll?

149
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:51,130
Did you tell Miss Marron?

150
00:14:53,805 --> 00:14:54,965
About the doll?

151
00:14:55,139 --> 00:14:59,542
We said there'd been an electrical
problem, like a short circuit.

152
00:15:01,145 --> 00:15:04,808
She doesn't need this kind of worry.
lt'd really upset her.

153
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:07,040
What about the police?

154
00:15:07,218 --> 00:15:09,209
No need. No one got hurt.

155
00:15:09,387 --> 00:15:10,877
The chauffeur got hurt.

156
00:15:11,389 --> 00:15:12,822
That was nothing.

157
00:15:13,724 --> 00:15:15,214
lt was just our people there.

158
00:15:16,661 --> 00:15:19,323
l think we should show him the room.

159
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,570
ls this her bedroom?

160
00:15:39,851 --> 00:15:42,911
She sleeps in the room next
to Fletcher's down the hall.

161
00:15:43,087 --> 00:15:45,681
Sy had this done for a magazine layout.

162
00:15:45,857 --> 00:15:47,586
Superstars in their boudoirs.

163
00:15:47,758 --> 00:15:48,850
Did you see it?

164
00:15:51,929 --> 00:15:53,521
We found the letter here.

165
00:15:57,735 --> 00:15:58,895
Someone was in here?

166
00:15:59,103 --> 00:16:02,197
Someone broke in and
masturbated on the bed.

167
00:16:05,543 --> 00:16:08,034
-And she doesn't know?
-Are you kidding?

168
00:16:08,212 --> 00:16:09,941
lt'd really freak her out.

169
00:16:10,114 --> 00:16:11,547
What do you think?

170
00:16:14,785 --> 00:16:17,117
Someone penetrates the house...

171
00:16:17,388 --> 00:16:20,551
...gets upstairs, jerks off on the bed.
l'd say...

172
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:22,619
...that qualifies as a problem.

173
00:16:22,793 --> 00:16:24,283
We don't need this.

174
00:16:24,529 --> 00:16:25,427
What kind?

175
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:28,722
-The house is wide open.
-Excuse me?

176
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,231
The house is wide open.

177
00:16:31,469 --> 00:16:35,235
You people have no clue what
security is or how to achieve it.

178
00:16:35,406 --> 00:16:37,738
l'll accommodate your work.

179
00:16:37,909 --> 00:16:39,308
l can't protect her like this.

180
00:16:39,477 --> 00:16:40,409
Like what?

181
00:16:41,979 --> 00:16:45,471
l won't be responsible for her safety
if she doesn't know what's going on.

182
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:46,739
l'll make her understand.

183
00:16:50,655 --> 00:16:52,088
l'll talk to her.

184
00:17:00,331 --> 00:17:03,266
She won't give you any static.
You have my word.

185
00:17:03,434 --> 00:17:04,492
Sure she will.

186
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:09,936
So what job's perfect?
You're a bodyguard, aren't you?

187
00:17:37,969 --> 00:17:40,631
Guess what? lt's Oscar time again.

188
00:17:40,805 --> 00:17:43,706
This year the money's on Rachel
Marron for best actress.

189
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:47,374
And with the theme song
of ''l Have Nothing''...

190
00:17:47,645 --> 00:17:49,203
...still big on the charts...

191
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:54,215
...the versatile actress/singer
might end up having everything.

192
00:18:19,844 --> 00:18:21,334
Why'd you say your name was Edison?

193
00:18:21,512 --> 00:18:24,072
To see how difficult it was to get in.

194
00:18:25,016 --> 00:18:26,176
And it wasn't.

195
00:18:39,697 --> 00:18:41,528
-Put it on your arm.
-What's this?

196
00:18:42,033 --> 00:18:43,432
lt'll stop the ache.

197
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:54,036
l bet you can fill up a whole day
washing cars and driving Miss Marron.

198
00:18:54,612 --> 00:18:55,772
That's my job.

199
00:18:57,448 --> 00:18:59,279
We're adding to your duties.

200
00:19:00,184 --> 00:19:01,811
You're my new assistant.

201
00:19:04,221 --> 00:19:05,119
Says who?

202
00:19:07,124 --> 00:19:11,788
l've spent a lot of time guarding people
and l've found one thing to be true.

203
00:19:12,563 --> 00:19:16,897
No matter how incompetent the assassins,
or how much they miss their target...

204
00:19:17,568 --> 00:19:19,559
...one person always gets hit.

205
00:19:20,971 --> 00:19:21,960
Who?

206
00:19:23,974 --> 00:19:25,305
The cocky black chauffeur.

207
00:19:28,079 --> 00:19:29,637
Put this in the pool.

208
00:19:41,592 --> 00:19:45,153
This gate will be replaced next week.
l'll have 2 cameras here.

209
00:19:45,329 --> 00:19:47,422
A face camera by the call box...

210
00:19:48,332 --> 00:19:51,324
...and a scene camera on top
of this pillar, looking down.

211
00:19:51,602 --> 00:19:56,164
l want these trees to be cut back so
the lights can shine onto the property.

212
00:19:56,340 --> 00:20:00,606
And the people who come into the
property, make sure who they are.

213
00:20:03,848 --> 00:20:06,009
l want these all cut back, okay?

214
00:20:06,183 --> 00:20:09,778
She paid a lot for the estate,
she ought to be able to see it.

215
00:20:12,289 --> 00:20:14,849
-What're you looking at?
-Frank.

216
00:20:15,359 --> 00:20:19,455
This fence is going to come around
this area and end by the gate.

217
00:20:21,365 --> 00:20:23,458
Come on. Let's go.

218
00:20:26,303 --> 00:20:29,636
Not yet, not yet, not yet. Now brake!

219
00:20:33,878 --> 00:20:34,867
Power.

220
00:20:36,647 --> 00:20:37,705
Stop.

221
00:21:02,339 --> 00:21:03,738
Come here!

222
00:21:04,575 --> 00:21:05,735
Come here.

223
00:21:07,912 --> 00:21:12,406
That's an unusual tactic for a
guard dog. But it's effective.

224
00:21:13,083 --> 00:21:15,574
You can look around if you want.

225
00:21:16,353 --> 00:21:17,411
Sorry to disturb you.

226
00:21:17,588 --> 00:21:20,182
lt's okay. lt's an excuse to rest.

227
00:21:20,925 --> 00:21:24,361
This is my personal place.
l'm the only one who works out here.

228
00:21:30,701 --> 00:21:33,602
My own ego wall.
No platinum records.

229
00:21:36,106 --> 00:21:37,869
This is you and Rachel?

230
00:21:39,777 --> 00:21:42,940
When l was a kid, l put
together this little band.

231
00:21:43,113 --> 00:21:45,775
We played school dances
and stuff like that.

232
00:21:47,618 --> 00:21:50,280
Rachel joined the act
and as you can imagine...

233
00:21:50,554 --> 00:21:52,784
...she was quite an entertainer.

234
00:21:54,892 --> 00:21:57,554
Even then she could stop the show.

235
00:21:58,128 --> 00:21:59,220
So....

236
00:21:59,463 --> 00:22:00,452
l quit.

237
00:22:00,631 --> 00:22:02,292
Professionally, anyway.

238
00:22:02,466 --> 00:22:03,956
You never went back?

239
00:22:04,235 --> 00:22:07,466
lt was pretty obvious who
the star in our family was.

240
00:22:12,743 --> 00:22:14,643
Lot of work went into this.

241
00:22:14,812 --> 00:22:15,904
Lot of work.

242
00:22:16,580 --> 00:22:18,138
No fingerprints, though.

243
00:22:18,749 --> 00:22:21,081
You think this is tied to the doll?

244
00:22:21,318 --> 00:22:22,979
Her manager does.

245
00:22:24,521 --> 00:22:27,456
''l have nothing'' is natural,
given the record, the movie.

246
00:22:33,430 --> 00:22:35,990
l lost track of you after Washington.

247
00:22:38,769 --> 00:22:40,600
How's the private stuff?

248
00:22:41,438 --> 00:22:42,769
lt's fine.

249
00:22:43,173 --> 00:22:44,333
Big money?

250
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:48,101
lt's big money, right?

251
00:22:48,612 --> 00:22:50,512
You wouldn't want this job.

252
00:22:52,516 --> 00:22:55,952
lt is big money! Fuck! l knew it!
You need an assistant?

253
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:59,954
l'm due to get out of here and l
have had it with assholic behavior.

254
00:23:00,124 --> 00:23:02,456
What a scumbag we're covering now.

255
00:23:02,626 --> 00:23:05,959
A walking schlong senator
who shall remain nameless.

256
00:23:06,130 --> 00:23:08,530
Hellfire Henry Kent.

257
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:10,364
Someone wants to pop him.

258
00:23:10,534 --> 00:23:13,367
No surprise, with what the
shithead's been saying.

259
00:23:13,537 --> 00:23:15,528
Do everyone a favor.

260
00:23:15,706 --> 00:23:18,539
As you know, we're
non-political these days.

261
00:23:20,144 --> 00:23:24,547
l'll send it to Behavioral Sciences.
l'll have an answer in a few days.

262
00:23:24,715 --> 00:23:25,704
Thanks.

263
00:23:27,484 --> 00:23:30,214
Why am l getting all this cooperation?

