00:50:17,092 --> 00:50:18,423
What happened?

534
00:50:18,761 --> 00:50:20,092
Do you mind if l ask?

535
00:50:20,262 --> 00:50:21,695
You mind if l don't answer?

536
00:50:24,767 --> 00:50:26,257
l don't want to pry.

537
00:50:26,435 --> 00:50:28,596
Oh, yeah, l can see that.

538
00:50:32,207 --> 00:50:33,196
What?

539
00:50:33,909 --> 00:50:36,104
She didn't die, did she?

540
00:50:38,013 --> 00:50:41,005
While you were protecting
her she got killed, right?

541
00:50:46,455 --> 00:50:48,787
God! That's not it, is it?

542
00:50:54,029 --> 00:50:55,621
That's it, isn't it?

543
00:50:57,566 --> 00:50:59,295
Nobody's perfect.

544
00:51:04,940 --> 00:51:06,805
l'm sorry, Frank.

545
00:51:07,876 --> 00:51:09,241
l'm sorry.

546
00:51:16,418 --> 00:51:17,942
Nice try, though.

547
00:51:24,426 --> 00:51:26,758
lt was less dramatic than that.

548
00:51:27,830 --> 00:51:29,764
She didn't love me anymore.

549
00:51:30,966 --> 00:51:32,593
Can you imagine that?

550
00:51:35,337 --> 00:51:37,328
No, not really.

551
00:51:53,188 --> 00:51:54,280
So...

552
00:51:54,623 --> 00:51:57,183
...is this a full-service date?

553
00:52:03,465 --> 00:52:05,695
l'm just asking you to dance.

554
00:52:09,204 --> 00:52:10,364
Come on.

555
00:52:12,941 --> 00:52:14,704
You can dance, can't you?

556
00:52:49,912 --> 00:52:52,403
This is kind of a cowboy song?

557
00:53:05,527 --> 00:53:07,256
Nothing. lt's nothing.

558
00:53:12,768 --> 00:53:16,761
l mean, it's so depressing.
Have you listened to the words?

559
00:53:24,379 --> 00:53:27,177
-lt is kind of depressing.
-Yes, it is.

560
00:53:28,450 --> 00:53:32,716
lt's one of those somebody's-
always-leaving-somebody songs.

561
00:53:43,565 --> 00:53:44,793
Don't worry.

562
00:53:46,635 --> 00:53:47,966
Don't worry.

563
00:53:48,203 --> 00:53:49,636
l'll protect you.

564
00:54:16,765 --> 00:54:18,596
lt's very quiet here.

565
00:54:26,775 --> 00:54:28,834
You ever going to hang these up?

566
00:54:31,346 --> 00:54:33,439
Maybe when l'm here long enough.

567
00:54:33,849 --> 00:54:37,012
West Virginia University Football.

568
00:54:37,986 --> 00:54:38,816
God!

569
00:54:39,354 --> 00:54:40,946
Take a look at you.

570
00:54:42,024 --> 00:54:43,252
What'd you play?

571
00:54:43,525 --> 00:54:44,685
The end.

572
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:46,850
Were you tough?

573
00:54:48,030 --> 00:54:50,021
No, l was fast.

574
00:54:59,107 --> 00:55:01,371
So you were in the Secret Service?

575
00:55:01,877 --> 00:55:03,174
What made you get out?

576
00:55:05,981 --> 00:55:07,175
Money.

577
00:55:09,551 --> 00:55:12,281
l can see your tastes are extravagant.

578
00:55:13,355 --> 00:55:14,219
May l?

579
00:55:40,482 --> 00:55:41,915
Be careful.

580
00:56:17,686 --> 00:56:20,018
You're a hard one to figure out.

581
00:56:26,028 --> 00:56:28,690
A bodyguard must know very little peace.

582
00:56:50,218 --> 00:56:51,549
Watch this.

583
00:57:38,066 --> 00:57:40,796
l've never felt this safe before.

584
00:57:43,905 --> 00:57:45,805
No one could get by you.

585
00:57:49,011 --> 00:57:51,571
Right now it might not be too difficult.

586
00:58:28,116 --> 00:58:29,640
What are you doing?

587
00:58:36,291 --> 00:58:39,454
l don't want to get confused
about what l'm doing here.

588
00:58:40,195 --> 00:58:42,026
l'm not confused.

589
00:58:42,464 --> 00:58:45,194
You pay me to protect you.
That's what l do.

590
00:58:48,670 --> 00:58:50,297
Did l do something wrong?

591
00:58:52,140 --> 00:58:53,129
Nothing.

592
00:58:54,409 --> 00:58:55,899
Then what is it?

593
00:58:58,580 --> 00:59:00,571
Do you want me to beg?

594
00:59:12,928 --> 00:59:14,862
What's going on, Frank?

595
00:59:16,064 --> 00:59:18,760
l want to keep straight what my job is.

596
00:59:18,934 --> 00:59:21,994
And what is that, exactly?
Making me feel like shit?

597
00:59:24,940 --> 00:59:26,498
l'm sorry, it's my fault.

598
00:59:26,775 --> 00:59:30,506
Don't apologize. Just tell me
what l did. l'm a big girl.

599
00:59:30,712 --> 00:59:32,236
You didn't do anything.

600
00:59:32,714 --> 00:59:34,079
lt was me.

601
00:59:35,183 --> 00:59:36,878
l got involved with my client.

602
00:59:37,018 --> 00:59:38,076
Your client?!

603
00:59:38,520 --> 00:59:40,078
l made a mistake.

604
00:59:41,022 --> 00:59:43,718
So you're not attracted
to your client anymore?

605
00:59:43,892 --> 00:59:45,951
Christ, l told you why!

606
00:59:46,962 --> 00:59:49,021
l can't protect you like this.

607
00:59:52,734 --> 00:59:54,531
So that's it for me?

608
00:59:55,637 --> 00:59:56,899
That's it?

609
01:00:01,977 --> 01:00:03,205
l don't believe it!

610
01:00:04,112 --> 01:00:05,909
Accept it, or fire me.

611
01:00:06,281 --> 01:00:07,805
But l can't fuck you.

612
01:00:22,297 --> 01:00:24,822
She's real mad at you, isn't she?

613
01:00:26,935 --> 01:00:30,564
She said she doesn't know why
you're being so shitty to her.

614
01:00:30,772 --> 01:00:33,240
l don't like you to use that language.

615
01:00:40,782 --> 01:00:45,082
l spent a lot of time learning not to
react to things like other people.

616
01:00:45,687 --> 01:00:47,245
That's my job.

617
01:00:48,323 --> 01:00:50,018
lt doesn't always work.

618
01:00:51,026 --> 01:00:52,960
lt doesn't always work.

619
01:00:54,596 --> 01:00:56,587
l don't think l understand.

620
01:00:57,599 --> 01:01:01,035
l'm an old man compared to you
and l don't understand either.

621
01:01:01,870 --> 01:01:04,031
l'm starting to get the feeling...

622
01:01:04,272 --> 01:01:05,864
...that l never will.

623
01:01:11,880 --> 01:01:13,347
l thought you'd like to know.

624
01:01:15,550 --> 01:01:19,042
Everyone said she was a sure thing.

625
01:01:19,888 --> 01:01:21,879
But you already knew that.

626
01:01:28,363 --> 01:01:32,629
Sorry. lt's completely out of line.
lt was none of my business.

627
01:01:47,148 --> 01:01:50,481
lt's off to Miami today for Best
Actress nominee Rachel Marron.

628
01:01:50,652 --> 01:01:55,146
She'll give two AlDS charity concerts
at the Fontainebleau Hilton.

629
01:01:55,323 --> 01:01:56,847
$1,000 a plate, no less.

630
01:01:57,025 --> 01:02:00,756
And it's a brave man who'd
deny she's worth every cent.

631
01:02:08,203 --> 01:02:11,695
This is Mobile 1 to Station 2.
Zero 2, engineering.

632
01:02:11,906 --> 01:02:15,740
Have them do a 14 reference to
presidential suite balcony.

633
01:02:19,881 --> 01:02:22,509
lt's okay. They're cleared.

634
01:02:23,685 --> 01:02:28,054
Mobile 2 to Catering. Security
says to clear kitchen aisle...

635
01:02:28,223 --> 01:02:31,886
...of all obstructions and traffic,
effective immediately.

636
01:02:32,694 --> 01:02:34,218
Mobile 2 to front of house.

637
01:02:34,362 --> 01:02:38,594
Security requests updated list of
all ticket holders for concert.

638
01:02:38,833 --> 01:02:43,532
Please fax copies of any names which are
added to the list to Security Office.

639
01:02:45,974 --> 01:02:48,135
What a silly job this is.

640
01:02:49,978 --> 01:02:51,843
Okay, we're rolling!

641
01:02:52,080 --> 01:02:54,139
-Showtime, everybody!
-ls this necessary?

642
01:02:54,316 --> 01:02:56,443
Yes, it is. Let's go.

643
01:02:58,320 --> 01:03:00,914
Quit bitching. You get paid for this.

644
01:03:01,089 --> 01:03:03,922
Rachel, can you give us
a couple of minutes?

645
01:03:04,092 --> 01:03:07,721
-How do you like our city?
-l love it! l love Miami!

646
01:04:49,564 --> 01:04:51,429
Did you arrange all this?

647
01:04:52,567 --> 01:04:54,364
Hey, that's me!

648
01:05:07,449 --> 01:05:08,279
Hello, Frank.

649
01:05:11,753 --> 01:05:13,277
lt's been a long time.

650
01:05:13,588 --> 01:05:14,850
You working?

651
01:05:15,690 --> 01:05:19,057
Not technically, but
the Governor may come...

652
01:05:19,227 --> 01:05:21,855
...so l thought l'd give a light check.

653
01:05:23,131 --> 01:05:25,065
Someone else is covering him now.

654
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:27,124
How old's she?

655
01:05:27,302 --> 01:05:28,701
Maybe 18.

656
01:05:37,712 --> 01:05:38,770
Thank you.

657
01:05:39,013 --> 01:05:42,244
Thank you so much.
Listen, you're so right.

658
01:05:43,551 --> 01:05:45,883
l want you all to have a good time...

659
01:05:46,087 --> 01:05:50,319
...and drink as much of Ben Schiller's
liquor as you possibly can.

660
01:05:50,625 --> 01:05:51,887
Thank you.

661
01:05:53,561 --> 01:05:56,428
l'd call that a step
up from the President.

662
01:05:57,499 --> 01:05:59,433
Probably sings better too.

663
01:06:01,302 --> 01:06:02,291
Handful.

664
01:06:05,106 --> 01:06:07,506
Lost track of you
after the Reagan thing.

665
01:06:11,746 --> 01:06:13,270
Wasn't your fault.

666
01:06:13,915 --> 01:06:15,576
You weren't even there.

667
01:06:21,456 --> 01:06:22,923
l need a drink.

668
01:06:30,832 --> 01:06:32,356
Orange juice.

669
01:06:33,201 --> 01:06:34,463
Who're you?

670
01:06:34,769 --> 01:06:35,929
Greg Portman.

671
01:06:37,071 --> 01:06:39,471
l take it you've met my bodyguard.

672
01:06:40,608 --> 01:06:42,473
We used to work together.

673
01:06:44,679 --> 01:06:46,306
Well, well, well.

674
01:06:46,848 --> 01:06:48,679
What do you do now?

675
01:06:49,083 --> 01:06:50,482
Same thing as Farmer.

676
01:06:51,486 --> 01:06:53,545
Two samurai, huh?

677
01:06:56,691 --> 01:06:58,556
So are you working now?

678
01:06:59,694 --> 01:07:01,161
Not right now.

679
01:07:01,696 --> 01:07:02,685
Good.

680
01:07:03,398 --> 01:07:06,799
Because l'm the only person in
this room that needs protection.

681
01:07:09,637 --> 01:07:12,333
Let's get a drink. A real one.

682
01:07:29,891 --> 01:07:31,415
Orange juice, sir?

683
01:07:37,832 --> 01:07:41,199
l've been watching you all
night from across the room.

684
01:07:44,272 --> 01:07:46,433
Why don't you go back and watch?

685
01:08:23,711 --> 01:08:25,702
No, l'm not doing this.

686
01:08:26,714 --> 01:08:27,703
You are.

687
01:08:32,654 --> 01:08:34,178
Please go now.

688
01:08:34,489 --> 01:08:35,956
Not right now.

689
01:08:38,326 --> 01:08:40,726
Mr. Portman was just leaving.

690
01:08:46,968 --> 01:08:48,492
Good night, Rachel.

691
01:09:05,987 --> 01:09:07,079
Shit.

692
01:10:05,146 --> 01:10:06,670
What are you looking at?

693
01:10:09,050 --> 01:10:12,679
You probably never had a heavy night
in your whole disciplined life.

694
01:10:13,888 --> 01:10:14,980
Coffee?

695
01:10:18,059 --> 01:10:20,755
You're a self-righteous bastard.

696
01:10:22,697 --> 01:10:24,995
Don't laugh! Don't dare judge me!

697
01:10:25,166 --> 01:10:28,693
Give me a break. l didn't tell
you to fuck everyone in the hotel!

698
01:10:29,370 --> 01:10:31,702
Fuck this. l don't need this shit.

699
01:10:38,146 --> 01:10:41,047
lndustrial detergent.
lt matches the traces in the glue.

700
01:10:42,350 --> 01:10:44,682
We'll nail this sucker.

701
01:10:45,219 --> 01:10:47,050
Don't take too long.

702
01:10:48,823 --> 01:10:50,518
lt's good money, isn't it?

703
01:10:52,527 --> 01:10:53,994
lt's good money.

704
01:11:24,559 --> 01:11:26,857
-Where is she?
-l don't know.

705
01:11:27,028 --> 01:11:30,725
-Where's Tony?
-l thought you were with her.

706
01:11:37,805 --> 01:11:41,104
Thuringer, this is Farmer.
Where's your man at the door?

707
01:11:42,043 --> 01:11:44,273
The door to the suite! Where is he?

708
01:11:45,813 --> 01:11:47,576
Get someone up here, now!

709
01:11:48,883 --> 01:11:49,872
He doesn't know.

710
01:11:50,051 --> 01:11:51,416
Where're you going?

711
01:11:58,826 --> 01:12:01,056
Where in the hell have you been?

712
01:12:02,230 --> 01:12:04,664
l went to Bal Harbor to shop.

713
01:12:04,832 --> 01:12:06,299
You want these in the bedroom?

714
01:12:06,500 --> 01:12:08,661
Leave them so l can look at them.

715
01:12:08,836 --> 01:12:11,964
You had us worried. You know
you're not supposed to do that.

716
01:12:12,773 --> 01:12:15,241
l'll do what l want when l want.

717
01:12:16,077 --> 01:12:17,442
Besides...

718
01:12:18,446 --> 01:12:20,778
...l'm tired of hanging
around deadbeats.

719
01:12:21,515 --> 01:12:22,675
No offense Tony.

720
01:12:28,990 --> 01:12:30,787
Once more and l'm gone.

721
01:12:30,992 --> 01:12:34,519
You remember something.
You work here. You work for me!

722
01:12:35,162 --> 01:12:36,527
Where're you going?

723
01:12:36,697 --> 01:12:38,790
To check the route, as usual.

724
01:12:42,436 --> 01:12:43,494
Did Fletcher call?

725
01:13:08,195 --> 01:13:09,560
Gomez!

726
01:13:23,511 --> 01:13:24,842
What are you doing?

727
01:13:24,979 --> 01:13:26,970
None of your fucking business.

728
01:13:28,182 --> 01:13:29,012
Move!

729
01:13:30,685 --> 01:13:32,516
Stick it up your ass!

730
01:13:48,402 --> 01:13:51,337
Stop! Don't hurt my husband, mister!

731
01:13:51,539 --> 01:13:54,997
Please, don't hurt my husband.
He not up to nothing.

732
01:14:07,555 --> 01:14:08,886
l'm sorry.

733
01:14:25,106 --> 01:14:26,095
Hello.

734
01:14:26,273 --> 01:14:27,365
Mommy?

735
01:14:28,442 --> 01:14:30,433
Fletcher, is that you?

736
01:14:38,919 --> 01:14:39,908
Listen.

737
01:14:40,654 --> 01:14:42,121
l'm through, Bill.

738
01:14:42,289 --> 01:14:45,281
l'm through. l'll get you
back to L.A. and that's it.

739
01:14:45,459 --> 01:14:47,586
Fletcher's guard'll cover you.

740
01:14:47,828 --> 01:14:49,921
She got another call.

741
01:14:50,398 --> 01:14:52,457
-l don't care.
-lt was him. Same guy.

742
01:14:52,666 --> 01:14:53,655
l don't care!

743
01:14:53,834 --> 01:14:58,294
lt really shook her up. She thought
it was Fletcher calling from L.A.

744
01:14:58,472 --> 01:15:01,236
l know she'll be reasonable now.
Come on.

745
01:15:01,409 --> 01:15:03,001
Save it, Devaney!

746
01:15:03,144 --> 01:15:07,137
Those who hire me don't have to be
convinced to save their own lives!

747
01:15:11,318 --> 01:15:13,081
Call me when she's ready.

748
01:15:52,726 --> 01:15:55,661
Nothing that's happened
between us matters.

749
01:15:59,066 --> 01:16:00,829
l understand now.

750
01:16:03,304 --> 01:16:06,671
You must believe me because
l'm not going to beg.

751
01:16:09,210 --> 01:16:11,075
lt wasn't what he said...

752
01:16:12,213 --> 01:16:14,078
...it was the way he said it.

753
01:16:16,550 --> 01:16:19,542
Frank, l need you. l'm afraid.

754
01:16:21,322 --> 01:16:23,153
And l hate my fear.

755
01:16:25,759 --> 01:16:28,227
Please protect me. Protect Fletcher.

756
01:16:28,496 --> 01:16:30,760
lf anything happened to him....

757
01:16:31,332 --> 01:16:32,697
l can't.

758
01:16:33,868 --> 01:16:35,028
l can't.

759
01:16:35,336 --> 01:16:37,770
l can't protect you like this.

760
01:16:39,507 --> 01:16:42,408
lt's impossible.
The odds are all on his side.

761
01:16:44,345 --> 01:16:46,779
l will do whatever you say.

762
01:16:55,956 --> 01:16:58,516
l'd want to take you away from here.

763
01:16:59,793 --> 01:17:01,260
l can do that.

764
01:17:07,201 --> 01:17:09,897
lt'd mean cancelling your concerts.

765
01:17:13,908 --> 01:17:14,966
All right.

766
01:17:16,277 --> 01:17:17,904
No more Sy.

767
01:17:21,448 --> 01:17:23,746
Give Devaney and Tony a vacation.

768
01:17:27,288 --> 01:17:28,380
Okay.

769
01:17:29,823 --> 01:17:33,281
You cross me up this time, l
swear l'll kill you myself.

770
01:18:33,821 --> 01:18:35,049
Lake's low.

771
01:18:36,490 --> 01:18:38,481
lt'll rise when it thaws.

772
01:18:47,067 --> 01:18:48,261
They all in trouble?

773
01:18:51,372 --> 01:18:52,634
Just one.

774
01:18:59,346 --> 01:19:01,337
He likes you.

775
01:19:01,782 --> 01:19:03,773
So is that going to protect us?

776
01:19:04,852 --> 01:19:07,184
He's a trained noisemaker.

777
01:19:07,421 --> 01:19:08,854
Come here, Foster.

778
01:19:09,189 --> 01:19:10,588
Just what we need.

779
01:19:10,791 --> 01:19:14,784
l don't like big dogs.
They don't know who they're eating.

780
01:19:14,928 --> 01:19:16,418
And this one does?

781
01:19:17,097 --> 01:19:19,031
Yeah, this one does.

782
01:19:31,378 --> 01:19:32,709
Excuse me.

783
01:19:33,447 --> 01:19:36,814
Katherine had this place
organized the way she wanted it.

784
01:19:37,618 --> 01:19:39,210
That's Frank's mama.

785
01:19:47,328 --> 01:19:49,728
Fletcher can't swim very well.

786
01:19:49,963 --> 01:19:52,227
He better stay in the boat then.

787
01:20:06,847 --> 01:20:08,246
Frank says you're a singer.

788
01:20:08,582 --> 01:20:09,981
That's right.

789
01:20:12,252 --> 01:20:15,483
We're kind of out of things up here.
l'm sorry.

790
01:20:15,656 --> 01:20:16,987
That's okay.

791
01:20:18,926 --> 01:20:22,157
You must be very successful if
you need someone like Frank.

792
01:20:25,999 --> 01:20:27,261
lt's quiet here.

793
01:20:28,168 --> 01:20:31,501
Frank spent 6 months here
after that Reagan thing.

794
01:20:32,606 --> 01:20:33,868
Reagan thing?

795
01:20:35,008 --> 01:20:38,444
Frank was gone when Reagan was shot.
He never got over it.

796
01:20:44,785 --> 01:20:47,117
That's the day we buried Katherine.

797
01:20:51,392 --> 01:20:52,882
He's a rascal now.

798
01:20:53,026 --> 01:20:54,015
Tell us.

799
01:20:54,962 --> 01:20:56,122
l never hit him.

800
01:20:56,296 --> 01:20:57,695
-Ever.
-You should have.

801
01:20:57,898 --> 01:21:00,196
That's unusual for my people.

802
01:21:00,634 --> 01:21:03,398
So what happens is, he's
about 10 years old...

803
01:21:03,537 --> 01:21:06,028
...and he starts complaining to me.

804
01:21:06,407 --> 01:21:07,465
How about that.

805
01:21:07,808 --> 01:21:11,039
Dad, l'll tell them about the
time you stripped in court.

806
01:21:11,211 --> 01:21:13,145
l want to hear this.

807
01:21:14,915 --> 01:21:16,473
l'm proud of that!

808
01:21:17,484 --> 01:21:20,476
So, anyway, he starts
playing tackle football...

809
01:21:20,654 --> 01:21:25,421
...when he's 10 and one day he comes to
me and says he's afraid of being hit.

810
01:21:25,826 --> 01:21:29,922
Says it's my fault. ''How come
you never hit me?'' he says to me.

811
01:21:30,164 --> 01:21:32,724
How about that? He got over it.

812
01:21:33,734 --> 01:21:36,168
Turned into one hell of a wide receiver.

813
01:21:36,737 --> 01:21:40,833
He was always like that, my son.
Couldn't stand being afraid.

814
01:21:41,008 --> 01:21:45,672
Something scared him, he'd just keep
doing it until the fear went away.

815
01:21:47,080 --> 01:21:49,514
His mama was the same way.

816
01:21:50,083 --> 01:21:51,516
You have a beautiful family.

817
01:21:51,752 --> 01:21:54,516
-You had enough to eat?
-Fletcher, wipe your mouth.

818
01:21:55,355 --> 01:21:57,516
-Save some for dessert.
-You through, bucket mouth?

819
01:21:57,691 --> 01:22:02,025
l won't tell about when you
were 13 and discovered girls.

820
01:22:07,768 --> 01:22:08,860
Come on.

821
01:22:09,203 --> 01:22:11,194
You can run but you can't hide.

822
01:22:16,210 --> 01:22:18,110
l'm black, right?

823
01:22:18,278 --> 01:22:20,769
You know you're white. Your move!

824
01:22:20,981 --> 01:22:22,972
My move? You're sure?

825
01:22:23,116 --> 01:22:25,778
The last move, l took your rook.

826
01:22:32,125 --> 01:22:33,285
That's right.

827
01:22:39,500 --> 01:22:41,627
How long has this been going on?

828
01:22:44,571 --> 01:22:45,560
3 years.

829
01:22:47,007 --> 01:22:49,498
First year he had me on the run.

830
01:22:53,814 --> 01:22:55,406
What do you think?

831
01:22:56,917 --> 01:22:58,316
Knight to king-four.

832
01:22:59,319 --> 01:23:00,411
City kid.

833
01:23:17,838 --> 01:23:20,170
Son, you come here and sit with me.

834
01:23:25,612 --> 01:23:28,342
Well, that's it for me, guys.
l'm going to bed.

835
01:23:28,615 --> 01:23:30,446
You're in trouble.

836
01:23:42,563 --> 01:23:45,054
Foster, right here. Turn around.

837
01:24:01,715 --> 01:24:03,148
Good night, Rachel.

838
01:24:04,217 --> 01:24:05,980
Good night, Frank.

839
01:24:06,153 --> 01:24:08,713
Good night, Foster. Good night.

840
01:24:11,091 --> 01:24:12,991
lt's good to hear you laugh.

841
01:24:18,332 --> 01:24:19,390
Stay.

842
01:24:41,121 --> 01:24:42,918
You're very thorough.

843
01:24:50,864 --> 01:24:53,025
What's happening with you and Rachel?

844
01:24:55,202 --> 01:24:58,535
One minute she has magnetic
hands and the next she hates you.

845
01:24:58,705 --> 01:25:01,037
l don't know what's going on now.

846
01:25:01,375 --> 01:25:03,707
You follow all her moves this closely?

847
01:25:06,546 --> 01:25:08,138
lt's a living.

848
01:25:09,149 --> 01:25:10,548
No, it's not.

849
01:25:17,724 --> 01:25:20,386
You must think my life's pretty sick.

850
01:25:22,462 --> 01:25:24,794
You must. l do.

851
01:25:26,066 --> 01:25:28,296
Then why don't you change it?

852
01:25:33,173 --> 01:25:34,800
ls it that easy?

853
01:25:49,089 --> 01:25:50,750
You're a lovely woman.

854
01:25:51,491 --> 01:25:53,186
But you don't want me?

855
01:25:57,097 --> 01:25:59,827
l'm surprised. Thorough fellow like you.

856
01:26:00,000 --> 01:26:02,696
Why stop at one sister when
you can fuck them both?

857
01:26:04,705 --> 01:26:06,696
l make my mistakes.

858
01:26:07,207 --> 01:26:09,334
But you didn't say no to the boss.

859
01:26:22,456 --> 01:26:23,855
ls this elk?

860
01:26:28,795 --> 01:26:30,228
A dear?

861
01:26:30,964 --> 01:26:32,295
Big.

862
01:26:41,808 --> 01:26:44,868
First time l've heard church
music in the middle of the week.

863
01:26:57,324 --> 01:27:01,988
Jesus loves me, oh, yes, he does.

864
01:27:06,333 --> 01:27:10,997
Jesus loves us, oh, yes, he does.

865
01:27:16,076 --> 01:27:20,775
Jesus loves us, oh, yes, he does.

866
01:27:25,352 --> 01:27:27,183
For the Bible...

867
01:27:27,420 --> 01:27:31,413
...tells me so.

868
01:27:34,928 --> 01:27:37,021
-Hi, kiddo.
-Hi, honey.

869
01:27:54,848 --> 01:27:56,145
Where's Fletcher?

870
01:28:28,081 --> 01:28:29,446
Help!

871
01:28:29,616 --> 01:28:30,810
He can't swim!

872
01:28:40,894 --> 01:28:42,191
Help!

873
01:28:43,463 --> 01:28:44,794
Help!

874
01:28:46,099 --> 01:28:47,726
Let me have him!

875
01:28:59,646 --> 01:29:01,204
What were you doing?

876
01:29:02,282 --> 01:29:03,977
You're crazy!

877
01:29:04,117 --> 01:29:05,277
You are out of your mind!

878
01:29:05,986 --> 01:29:09,285
You could have drowned him!
You could have drowned him!

879
01:29:09,656 --> 01:29:10,987
l'm sorry.

880
01:29:12,592 --> 01:29:13,923
l got careless.

881
01:29:17,297 --> 01:29:19,288
How will we get the boat back?

882
01:29:29,142 --> 01:29:31,133
Put them in there.

883
01:29:41,087 --> 01:29:45,319
Someone's cut the phone lines. Could
be anywhere between here and town.

884
01:29:45,625 --> 01:29:48,321
Both cars are dead. l don't see how.

885
01:29:50,463 --> 01:29:52,158
Who knows you're here?

886
01:29:52,799 --> 01:29:55,461
l don't know. This place
has nothing to do with her.

887
01:29:56,036 --> 01:29:58,163
Maybe it has to do with you.

888
01:30:00,273 --> 01:30:02,798
And we can't walk out of here at night.

889
01:30:02,976 --> 01:30:04,034
l know.

890
01:30:04,811 --> 01:30:07,439
We'll stay and walk out at first light.

891
01:31:26,059 --> 01:31:28,118
l was an idiot last night.

892
01:31:33,633 --> 01:31:36,124
What'd you think about today?

893
01:31:43,443 --> 01:31:45,570
l think this is no maniac.

894
01:31:47,380 --> 01:31:48,904
He knows what he's doing.

895
01:31:50,750 --> 01:31:52,445
You're right. He does.

896
01:31:56,156 --> 01:31:57,589
Tell me about it.

897
01:31:58,925 --> 01:32:01,155
-Who is it?
-He almost got Fletcher...

898
01:32:01,294 --> 01:32:02,659
How do we stop him?

899
01:32:02,829 --> 01:32:05,389
-He almost got the baby!
-Who is it?

900
01:32:05,598 --> 01:32:07,088
l don't know.

901
01:32:07,233 --> 01:32:08,393
Call it off.

902
01:32:08,601 --> 01:32:11,399
He doesn't even know who hired him.

903
01:32:13,006 --> 01:32:16,100
l don't know who he is and
he doesn't know who l am.

904
01:32:17,010 --> 01:32:18,773
How did you do it?

905
01:32:19,679 --> 01:32:20,839
How?

906
01:32:21,014 --> 01:32:23,312
l went to a bar in East L.A.

907
01:32:25,251 --> 01:32:28,243
l asked around. And there was this guy.

908
01:32:28,421 --> 01:32:29,410
Name?

909
01:32:29,689 --> 01:32:31,418
-Armando.
-Give me his name!

910
01:32:32,258 --> 01:32:33,486
Armando.

911
01:32:38,698 --> 01:32:41,132
He arranged it, that's all l know.

912
01:32:42,202 --> 01:32:43,430
lt's all paid?

913
01:32:47,273 --> 01:32:48,433
ls it paid for?

914
01:32:48,641 --> 01:32:51,508
And then some, okay? Till it's done.

915
01:32:53,880 --> 01:32:56,212
He keeps going until he kills her?

916
01:32:59,986 --> 01:33:03,444
-What's the name of the bar?
-l'm not sure.

917
01:33:03,723 --> 01:33:04,815
l was stoned.

918
01:33:07,894 --> 01:33:10,829
All right. How about the letters?

919
01:33:11,364 --> 01:33:15,164
The letters came first. l don't
know who's writing the letters.

920
01:33:15,368 --> 01:33:18,064
Shit, but they're reading my mind.

921
01:33:18,371 --> 01:33:21,534
Those are my thoughts. l hate her.

922
01:33:25,245 --> 01:33:27,543
lt made me think l could do it.

923
01:33:28,681 --> 01:33:32,674
But l would never hurt the baby.
l would never hurt Fletcher!

924
01:33:32,852 --> 01:33:33,841
l know.

925
01:33:36,189 --> 01:33:38,020
You must stop it.

926
01:33:38,191 --> 01:33:39,180
We will.

927
01:33:39,559 --> 01:33:41,026
You and me.

928
01:33:49,936 --> 01:33:52,029
Don't you want to know why?

929
01:33:52,705 --> 01:33:54,036
You told me.

930
01:33:54,140 --> 01:33:55,368
She has everything.

931
01:34:01,281 --> 01:34:03,272
What if we can't find him?

932
01:34:09,422 --> 01:34:11,515
Stay here and don't move.

933
01:34:28,074 --> 01:34:29,598
-lt's me!
-God!

934
01:34:30,310 --> 01:34:31,743
What's happening?

935
01:34:32,378 --> 01:34:33,367
Stay with her!

936
01:34:33,613 --> 01:34:36,980
-Where's Nicki?
-No! No, stop! l'm the one--

937
01:34:53,466 --> 01:34:55,400
-Dad?
-We're okay.

938
01:36:13,913 --> 01:36:16,245
-Doesn't make sense.
-What do you mean?

939
01:36:16,416 --> 01:36:17,474
We got him.

940
01:36:17,717 --> 01:36:19,708
What do you mean? Where?

941
01:36:19,919 --> 01:36:23,411
Here. Last night. ln L.A.
You should see this guy's locker.

942
01:36:23,556 --> 01:36:25,251
He's obsessed with her.

943
01:36:25,425 --> 01:36:26,722
You sure it's him?

944
01:36:26,926 --> 01:36:29,258
Forensics say a 100% positive lD.

945
01:36:29,662 --> 01:36:31,857
And he's got a black Toyota 4 x 4.

946
01:36:32,031 --> 01:36:33,555
We know you did it.

947
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:35,667
Ray's with him now.

948
01:36:36,736 --> 01:36:41,264
lt's you that sent her the letters.
We don't need you to admit it.

949
01:36:41,441 --> 01:36:42,499
We know!

950
01:36:43,509 --> 01:36:44,737
We know it!

951
01:36:44,944 --> 01:36:49,574
Whoever you got down there wasn't here
last night. This was a professional.

952
01:36:50,216 --> 01:36:51,513
This is crazy.

953
01:36:51,684 --> 01:36:53,276
What do you want to do?

954
01:36:55,455 --> 01:36:56,683
How long can you keep him?

955
01:36:57,390 --> 01:36:59,756
All he's done is write some letters.

956
01:37:00,126 --> 01:37:02,890
48 hours maximum. You know the deal.

957
01:37:04,697 --> 01:37:05,891
l know.

958
01:37:12,171 --> 01:37:16,631
Strict security surrounded the funeral
of music executive Nicki Marron...

959
01:37:17,443 --> 01:37:21,436
...who was shot at a lakeside
retreat by an unknown intruder.

960
01:37:21,581 --> 01:37:24,573
Nicki was the eldest
sister of Rachel Marron.

961
01:37:24,751 --> 01:37:29,120
A spokesman for the Oscar-nominated
actress said she was devastated...

962
01:37:29,288 --> 01:37:33,588
...and added that naturally it cast a
pall over the upcoming award ceremony.

963
01:38:49,202 --> 01:38:50,362
You okay?

964
01:38:52,038 --> 01:38:55,667
Yeah, Fletcher, l'm okay.
How about yourself?

965
01:38:57,443 --> 01:38:59,274
l couldn't sleep.

966
01:39:01,380 --> 01:39:04,213
lt was so scary, just thinking about it.

967
01:39:06,285 --> 01:39:08,276
Are you scared?

968
01:39:09,155 --> 01:39:11,146
Everybody's afraid of something.

969
01:39:13,292 --> 01:39:16,056
That's how we know we
care about things...

970
01:39:17,063 --> 01:39:18,690
...when we're scared to lose them.

971
01:39:20,766 --> 01:39:22,233
What are you afraid of?

972
01:39:24,871 --> 01:39:27,704
l think you should try
to go back to sleep.

973
01:39:30,776 --> 01:39:33,244
ls it the man who killed Nicki?

974
01:39:35,414 --> 01:39:37,314
Are you afraid of him?

975
01:39:40,486 --> 01:39:41,783
Then what?

976
01:39:43,256 --> 01:39:45,190
What are you afraid of?

977
01:39:52,098 --> 01:39:53,793
l'm afraid of not...

978
01:39:55,434 --> 01:39:56,731
...being there.

979
01:40:03,276 --> 01:40:06,268
lt's late. Want me to
take you up to your room?

980
01:41:01,567 --> 01:41:03,034
May l sit down?

981
01:41:16,682 --> 01:41:18,411
lt isn't over yet, is it?

982
01:41:22,054 --> 01:41:23,578
So he'll come again?

983
01:41:24,890 --> 01:41:26,289
lt's possible.

984
01:41:27,693 --> 01:41:28,717
At the Oscars?

985
01:41:30,596 --> 01:41:31,756
Maybe.

986
01:41:36,369 --> 01:41:38,064
Back in Squirrel Hill...

987
01:41:39,372 --> 01:41:44,207
...l started betting my friends 50 bucks
each that someday l'd win an Oscar.

988
01:41:46,078 --> 01:41:49,912
So it's very important for them
to see me up there if l win.

989
01:41:51,550 --> 01:41:55,850
lf every one of those pikers comes
through, it'd add up to a lot of money.

990
01:42:01,727 --> 01:42:03,456
l don't know, Rachel.

991
01:42:03,796 --> 01:42:05,787
l think it's still dangerous.

992
01:42:05,931 --> 01:42:09,458
l didn't get here by doing
the smart thing every time.

993
01:42:13,239 --> 01:42:14,399
How about you?

994
01:42:17,109 --> 01:42:19,236
Out there on the edge.

995
01:42:19,412 --> 01:42:22,745
Haven't you done something
that didn't make sense...

996
01:42:24,950 --> 01:42:27,475
...except inside you? ln your stomach?

997
01:42:31,490 --> 01:42:32,957
l know you have.

998
01:42:33,592 --> 01:42:36,060
Because no one gets good without it.

999
01:42:36,829 --> 01:42:38,262
And l know you're good.

1000
01:42:44,070 --> 01:42:45,128
Look...

1001
01:42:46,138 --> 01:42:48,663
...l don't know why this is happening...

1002
01:42:50,609 --> 01:42:52,975
...but l know it's not your fault.

1003
01:42:53,512 --> 01:42:57,505
And l hope you can hear me because
this is the way l say l'm sorry.

1004
01:42:59,285 --> 01:43:00,445
So...

1005
01:43:01,520 --> 01:43:04,080
...l'm going to the
Oscars and see if l win.

1006
01:43:05,091 --> 01:43:08,083
And l won't worry about
it at all, because...

1007
01:43:08,861 --> 01:43:10,852
...l have you to protect me.

1008
01:43:12,798 --> 01:43:14,095
That's right.

1009
01:43:19,004 --> 01:43:20,301
That's right.

1010
01:44:04,517 --> 01:44:07,975
We'll go straight back to the Green Room.
Got that, Tony?

1011
01:44:08,354 --> 01:44:09,844
Tony knows what he's doing.

1012
01:44:10,689 --> 01:44:14,853
l wish you guys would relax.
Nothing bad's going to happen.

1013
01:44:15,361 --> 01:44:16,453
Right?

1014
01:44:17,363 --> 01:44:19,160
Unless l lose the award.

1015
01:44:22,535 --> 01:44:23,934
Jesus, what a crew!

1016
01:44:27,473 --> 01:44:28,770
Screw it.

1017
01:44:29,008 --> 01:44:30,942
l'm tired of worrying.

1018
01:44:31,243 --> 01:44:32,870
When your time is up...

1019
01:44:33,946 --> 01:44:35,072
...it's up.

1020
01:44:36,182 --> 01:44:37,547
Right, Frank?

1021
01:45:01,574 --> 01:45:04,042
-Rachel Marron, how are you?
-Fine. And you?

1022
01:45:04,210 --> 01:45:05,575
Good. You look lovely.

1023
01:45:05,744 --> 01:45:07,803
-Thank you.
-And they love you, don't they?

1024
01:45:07,980 --> 01:45:09,208
They're going wild!

1025
01:45:09,415 --> 01:45:11,906
So are you the queen of this night?

1026
01:45:12,051 --> 01:45:13,279
Let's hope so.

1027
01:45:14,220 --> 01:45:18,213
Good luck. Everybody's pulling for you.
Rachel Marron, everybody.

1028
01:45:24,430 --> 01:45:28,230
And the award for best
achievement in sound...

1029
01:45:28,934 --> 01:45:30,424
...goes to...

1030
01:45:30,603 --> 01:45:32,230
...Kay Colvin...

1031
01:45:32,438 --> 01:45:35,430
...and Mychal Smith for ''Hot and Cold.''

1032
01:45:56,695 --> 01:45:58,560
Thank you so much.

1033
01:45:58,964 --> 01:46:01,159
l want to thank our producers.

1034
01:46:04,169 --> 01:46:07,866
There is a gap, house left, rows EE FF.
Get me some fillers.

1035
01:46:10,709 --> 01:46:14,042
You look beautiful. l just need to
tell you your responsibilities.

1036
01:46:16,181 --> 01:46:18,877
Now it's Best Sound.
Then a song, then you.

1037
01:46:19,051 --> 01:46:22,350
At 8:07, you will be
presenting with Clive Healy.

1038
01:46:23,055 --> 01:46:24,488
Your lines.

1039
01:46:24,723 --> 01:46:28,056
The TelePrompTer is straight ahead
and, we pray, working perfectly.

1040
01:46:30,729 --> 01:46:34,495
l understand it's my honor
to escort you on stage.

1041
01:46:34,733 --> 01:46:38,897
That's right and l don't like it one
bit that you look skinnier than me.

1042
01:46:39,071 --> 01:46:40,299
l wish.

1043
01:46:40,839 --> 01:46:43,307
How's the Hollywood cricket scene?

1044
01:46:43,509 --> 01:46:48,378
Coming out of commercial. Five,
four, three, two. Cue music.

1045
01:46:49,682 --> 01:46:51,149
Cue Robert.

1046
01:46:54,019 --> 01:46:56,078
Welcome back to the Academy Awards.

1047
01:46:56,221 --> 01:46:57,688
Stand by, dancers.

1048
01:46:57,856 --> 01:47:01,223
l just heard that in New York
the economy is so bad...

1049
01:47:01,393 --> 01:47:04,521
...that the Mafia has
laid off five judges.

1050
01:47:07,399 --> 01:47:10,527
l'm going to look around,
then come back for her.

1051
01:47:12,171 --> 01:47:13,866
No more carrots.

1052
01:47:14,340 --> 01:47:16,638
Did you like the couple that just won?

1053
01:47:16,775 --> 01:47:19,710
Did you ever see a woman on
sound that looked like that?

1054
01:47:20,112 --> 01:47:22,171
She must have been the boom girl.

1055
01:47:22,948 --> 01:47:25,712
Looked like the bada-bing-bada-boom
girl right there.

1056
01:47:25,884 --> 01:47:28,250
lf she's working sound, who's listening?

1057
01:47:28,554 --> 01:47:29,782
Lighting change.

1058
01:47:29,955 --> 01:47:33,550
And he was eloquent: ''lt's the
most happiest day of my life.''

1059
01:47:33,726 --> 01:47:37,355
Bet his mother was very
most proudest of him then.

1060
01:47:37,563 --> 01:47:38,723
20 seconds.

1061
01:47:42,201 --> 01:47:43,896
Hi, Frank. How are you?

1062
01:47:44,269 --> 01:47:45,361
Why're you here?

1063
01:47:45,971 --> 01:47:47,905
-On the job.
-Who?

1064
01:47:49,742 --> 01:47:50,731
Him.

1065
01:47:51,377 --> 01:47:52,810
Short-term gig, but...

1066
01:47:53,679 --> 01:47:54,907
...profitable.

1067
01:47:57,816 --> 01:48:00,284
Frank, l'm sorry about Miami.

1068
01:48:02,454 --> 01:48:04,217
Cue music.

1069
01:48:05,624 --> 01:48:07,114
Cue dancers.

1070
01:48:15,401 --> 01:48:16,698
Back to work.

1071
01:48:17,169 --> 01:48:19,262
See you at the Governor's ball.

1072
01:48:31,450 --> 01:48:33,441
She sounds great.

1073
01:48:33,685 --> 01:48:36,176
l want her run out of town.

1074
01:48:36,488 --> 01:48:37,648
She must go!

1075
01:48:38,590 --> 01:48:39,989
Tony, you there?

1076
01:48:41,693 --> 01:48:42,751
Tony?

1077
01:48:43,695 --> 01:48:48,155
l have a feeling this is the night.
He'll go for her on camera.

1078
01:48:48,434 --> 01:48:49,594
That's crazy!

1079
01:48:49,768 --> 01:48:53,704
That's how he wants it to look;
but he's not crazy, he's very clever.

1080
01:48:53,872 --> 01:48:56,432
Listen, l need you to help me tonight.

1081
01:48:56,608 --> 01:49:00,009
You can't use that thing.
There's bad breakthrough.

1082
01:49:00,179 --> 01:49:01,874
l must disconnect you.

1083
01:49:03,015 --> 01:49:04,004
l'll do it.

1084
01:49:05,951 --> 01:49:08,078
You get it back after the show.

1085
01:49:20,232 --> 01:49:21,221
What's wrong?

1086
01:49:21,400 --> 01:49:22,697
Ready to go?

1087
01:49:23,802 --> 01:49:25,030
Shall we go?

1088
01:49:25,370 --> 01:49:28,100
Gentlemen, is this necessary?
Must we have everyone?

1089
01:49:28,273 --> 01:49:30,741
We have our own man at the door!

1090
01:49:31,210 --> 01:49:32,268
Please.

1091
01:49:32,978 --> 01:49:34,969
No, l want him.

1092
01:49:37,983 --> 01:49:39,041
Fine.

1093
01:49:41,653 --> 01:49:43,052
Stay alert.

1094
01:49:45,491 --> 01:49:47,220
Let us brighten this firmament.

1095
01:50:04,243 --> 01:50:08,009
Coming through, please.
How much time do we have?

1096
01:50:08,580 --> 01:50:10,070
Resetting staircases.

1097
01:50:11,316 --> 01:50:12,943
Scenery coming in.

1098
01:50:13,085 --> 01:50:14,677
30 seconds to lighting change.

1099
01:50:19,958 --> 01:50:23,325
30 seconds. Don't panic.
Clear this area, please.

1100
01:50:28,700 --> 01:50:31,328
Rachel, up, to the right and through.

1101
01:50:32,037 --> 01:50:36,701
Clive, up, to the left and through.
You'll meet on the landing.

1102
01:50:37,609 --> 01:50:40,601
Watch your step going down.
Somebody spilled water.

1103
01:50:44,616 --> 01:50:45,708
Shall we?

1104
01:50:54,193 --> 01:50:57,458
Do try to relax. l know
you must be very excited.

1105
01:50:58,063 --> 01:50:59,189
Thank you.

1106
01:51:04,002 --> 01:51:06,300
Presenting the Best Song award are...

1107
01:51:06,471 --> 01:51:08,132
...Hollywood's newest couple.

1108
01:51:08,307 --> 01:51:10,571
He's England's knight in shining armor.

1109
01:51:10,842 --> 01:51:13,572
She's America's queen of the night.

1110
01:51:13,812 --> 01:51:17,270
Please welcome Clive
Healy and Rachel Marron.

1111
01:51:45,377 --> 01:51:46,742
Well, Rachel....

1112
01:51:46,912 --> 01:51:51,372
l know you only came to present this
award and you'll leave when we're done.

1113
01:52:00,759 --> 01:52:04,661
No, l'm very interested in
one of the awards tonight.

1114
01:52:05,130 --> 01:52:06,119
Best Actor.

1115
01:52:09,868 --> 01:52:13,167
Tonight we heard 5 songs and
the names of their creators.

1116
01:52:20,579 --> 01:52:24,515
No matter what anyone thinks.
l know you have no personal favorites.

1117
01:52:26,118 --> 01:52:28,052
The Best Song nominees are...

1118
01:52:28,253 --> 01:52:32,952
...''Clock On The Wall'' by Dana S.
Lee and Sarah Spring...

1119
01:52:36,261 --> 01:52:39,958
...''Give Me Your Trust'' by David
Siegel and Barbara Gordon...

1120
01:52:45,971 --> 01:52:47,370
...''l Have Nothing''...

1121
01:52:47,539 --> 01:52:50,269
...''Queen of the Night''
by Nancy Garber...

1122
01:52:53,545 --> 01:52:57,982
...and ''Reflections of My Heart'' from
''Hot and Cold'' by Leslie Moraes.

1123
01:53:03,221 --> 01:53:06,156
All right, Clive, let's find out...

1124
01:53:08,093 --> 01:53:09,458
...who the winner is.

1125
01:53:09,728 --> 01:53:12,561
The envelope. Rachel,
shall l do the honors?

1126
01:53:23,875 --> 01:53:25,775
And the winner is:
''l Have Nothing''...

1127
01:53:25,877 --> 01:53:28,937
...from ''Queen of the Night''
by Nancy Garber.

1128
01:53:35,754 --> 01:53:37,244
She's good, Frank.

1129
01:53:41,126 --> 01:53:42,184
l'm okay.

1130
01:53:42,861 --> 01:53:44,351
l always said she was nuts.

1131
01:53:44,863 --> 01:53:46,421
l'm okay, all right?

1132
01:53:47,065 --> 01:53:49,863
You're making me
into a raving lunatic!

1133
01:53:51,470 --> 01:53:52,459
God!

1134
01:53:53,872 --> 01:53:54,861
You okay?

1135
01:53:55,040 --> 01:53:56,268
Yes!

1136
01:53:57,275 --> 01:53:58,765
Fucking actresses!

1137
01:54:00,278 --> 01:54:02,041
-Where's Portman?
-Who?

1138
01:54:02,214 --> 01:54:04,148
-Portman.
-Never heard of him.

1139
01:54:10,689 --> 01:54:15,217
l'm sorry, but if you want to be in your
seat for Best Actress, you must go now.

1140
01:54:15,360 --> 01:54:19,353
l'm going as fast as l can. Why don't
you go twitch somewhere else?

1141
01:54:19,531 --> 01:54:21,999
Everything's fine. No one noticed.

1142
01:54:22,300 --> 01:54:25,701
-Everyone's jumping out of their skins.
-Bullshit.

1143
01:54:25,904 --> 01:54:28,236
Farmer's making me into a lunatic!

1144
01:54:28,373 --> 01:54:30,705
-You should know--
-You're driving her crazy!

1145
01:54:31,309 --> 01:54:32,640
l know who it is.

1146
01:54:32,811 --> 01:54:34,711
-Shut up!
-He's here tonight!

1147
01:54:35,180 --> 01:54:39,549
You're a maniac! You've embarrassed
me in front of billions of people.

1148
01:54:41,920 --> 01:54:44,650
-Wait for Frank. Honey, please.
-Three minutes!

1149
01:54:44,823 --> 01:54:46,381
Calm the fuck down!

1150
01:54:46,558 --> 01:54:48,082
ls he coming?

1151
01:54:53,565 --> 01:54:54,930
l know who it is.

1152
01:54:55,100 --> 01:54:56,089
Portman.

1153
01:54:56,268 --> 01:54:58,736
Remember? The guy in Miami.

1154
01:54:59,271 --> 01:55:02,263
-Oh, yeah, the pencil neck!
-ls anyone coming with me?

1155
01:55:02,507 --> 01:55:06,409
After tonight, you're in charge.
He knows nothing about show business.

1156
01:55:06,578 --> 01:55:08,569
Two minutes to Best Actress.

1157
01:55:10,282 --> 01:55:12,113
You're an asshole.

1158
01:55:13,752 --> 01:55:15,845
To present the Best Actress award...

1159
01:55:16,521 --> 01:55:21,220
...we have the man who last year, won
for his performance in ''South of Waco''...

1160
01:55:21,359 --> 01:55:24,351
Ladies and gentlemen, please
welcome Mr. Tom Winston.

1161
01:55:35,707 --> 01:55:37,072
Thank you, Academy.

1162
01:55:37,876 --> 01:55:39,241
Did you see him?

1163
01:55:39,978 --> 01:55:43,311
-Go to the other side of the stage.
-What do l do?

1164
01:55:44,316 --> 01:55:45,613
See those people?

1165
01:55:45,884 --> 01:55:47,545
They don't need to be there.

1166
01:55:47,719 --> 01:55:49,710
That guy with the camera too.

1167
01:55:50,255 --> 01:55:52,086
l'll take care of it.

1168
01:55:55,393 --> 01:55:57,725
Rachel Marron for ''Queen of the Night.''

1169
01:56:10,909 --> 01:56:11,898
You!

1170
01:56:14,913 --> 01:56:16,904
Rachel Marron!

1171
01:56:17,349 --> 01:56:19,180
''Queen of the Night.''

1172
01:57:36,261 --> 01:57:37,728
Go to commercial.

1173
01:57:37,896 --> 01:57:39,488
He's got a gun!

1174
01:57:39,731 --> 01:57:40,698
He's got a gun!

1175
01:57:42,734 --> 01:57:43,826
Get the gun!

1176
01:58:09,594 --> 01:58:11,755
-She's bleeding!
-lt's not me!

1177
01:58:13,765 --> 01:58:15,392
He's my bodyguard!

1178
01:58:26,044 --> 01:58:28,137
Frank! Stay with me!

1179
01:58:28,413 --> 01:58:31,041
Stay with me! Come on.

1180
01:58:31,716 --> 01:58:34,048
God, hurry up!

1181
01:59:50,929 --> 01:59:51,918
How's it going?

1182
01:59:52,931 --> 01:59:54,296
lt's under control.

1183
01:59:55,300 --> 01:59:57,291
lt won't be the same without you.

1184
01:59:59,003 --> 02:00:00,402
How you doing?

1185
02:00:14,652 --> 02:00:16,552
You shouldn't be here.

1186
02:00:18,890 --> 02:00:20,721
So you're quitting show business?

1187
02:00:21,893 --> 02:00:24,418
Too bad. You had talent.

1188
02:00:28,600 --> 02:00:31,125
Fletcher, go to the plane.

1189
02:00:35,140 --> 02:00:36,505
How's the new guy?

1190
02:00:38,843 --> 02:00:40,674
He's got white hair.

1191
02:00:42,914 --> 02:00:45,974
-He's very good.
-But did you have to get me an old man?

1192
02:00:46,918 --> 02:00:48,715
l don't trust you.

1193
02:01:02,700 --> 02:01:05,863
Let's get this over with,
okay? Give me a kiss.

1194
02:01:12,777 --> 02:01:14,074
Goodbye, Rachel.

1195
02:01:15,780 --> 02:01:17,372
'Bye, Frank.

1196
02:01:25,957 --> 02:01:28,619
lf l should stay

1197
02:01:34,632 --> 02:01:36,099
l would only...

1198
02:01:37,035 --> 02:01:38,263
...be in...

1199
02:01:39,737 --> 02:01:41,261
...your way

1200
02:01:43,408 --> 02:01:46,036
So l'll go.

1201
02:01:46,211 --> 02:01:47,576
You okay?

1202
02:01:48,213 --> 02:01:50,204
But l know...

1203
02:01:52,050 --> 02:01:54,109
...l'll think of you.

1204
02:01:54,285 --> 02:01:56,116
Every step of...

1205
02:01:57,589 --> 02:01:59,420
...the way

1206
02:02:06,064 --> 02:02:07,053
Wait!

1207
02:02:15,607 --> 02:02:18,940
And l will always love you

1208
02:02:36,261 --> 02:02:38,252
You, my darling you

1209
02:02:43,268 --> 02:02:44,860
Bittersweet...

1210
02:02:46,704 --> 02:02:48,331
...memories

1211
02:02:50,475 --> 02:02:52,466
That is all...

1212
02:02:52,710 --> 02:02:55,338
...l'm taking with me

1213
02:02:57,582 --> 02:02:59,345
So goodbye.

1214
02:03:00,885 --> 02:03:03,183
Please don't cry.

1215
02:03:04,656 --> 02:03:06,487
We both know...

1216
02:03:06,724 --> 02:03:09,659
...l'm not what you need

1217
02:03:17,602 --> 02:03:20,503
And l will always love you

1218
02:03:32,016 --> 02:03:35,918
Our speaker this evening has
been a lone courageous voice.

1219
02:03:36,220 --> 02:03:40,680
He alone has challenged those
who have linked organized crime...

1220
02:03:41,092 --> 02:03:44,084
...with legitimate business
throughout our state.

1221
02:03:44,529 --> 02:03:46,224
Welcome, Congressman.

1222
02:03:53,771 --> 02:03:58,174
First our benediction will be delivered
by the Reverend Phillip Hardy...

1223
02:03:58,409 --> 02:04:02,106
...of the First Presbyterian
Church of lowa Rapids.

1224
02:04:06,417 --> 02:04:08,180
Heavenly Father...

1225
02:04:08,653 --> 02:04:12,350
...please bless us today as we
meet in friendship and duty.

1226
02:04:13,424 --> 02:04:17,053
And, Lord, whatever dangerous
endeavors those among us may take...

1227
02:04:17,195 --> 02:04:20,130
...let them never be
without Your sanctuary.

1228
02:04:21,132 --> 02:04:22,793
We know in our hearts...

1229
02:04:22,967 --> 02:04:26,368
...that though we may pass through
the valley of the shadow of death...

1230
02:04:26,571 --> 02:04:28,266
...You are with us...

1231
02:04:28,439 --> 02:04:31,067
...guiding and protecting us.

1232
02:04:32,143 --> 02:04:33,371
Amen.

